# Repository Structure

**Project**: WebRTC Engineering — demos and projects repository

> **Single Source of Truth**: [docs/01-repository-structure.md](../../docs/01-repository-structure.md)

## Quick Summary

- **`src/<topic>/`**: Study modules (notes, snippets) — `fundamentals/`, `signaling/`, `networking/`, etc.
- **`demos/NNN-name/`**: Numbered runnable WebRTC labs (`001-getusermedia/`, …).
- **`projects/pNN-name/`**: Larger integrated apps (`p01-video-call/`, …).
- **`docs/`**: Architecture, notes, diagrams, RFC summaries.
- **`experiments/`**: Codecs, bandwidth, packet-loss, simulcast, SFU, load-testing.
- **`tools/`**: Coturn, Docker, scripts (PowerShell maintenance).
- **`assets/`**: Shared images, diagrams, videos.

Do not list internal-only paths in public-facing docs.

## Preserved archives

- `.archive/` — legacy tooling and content; leave unless Swamy asks to migrate.
